He opened his mail.

00:16:40.720 --> 00:16:42.020
He tailed his family.

00:16:42.020 --> 00:16:46.530
He tried to get a woman to
lure him into a hotel room

00:16:46.530 --> 00:16:50.010
where he could photographed,
all of this has failed.

00:16:50.010 --> 00:16:53.970
However, Thomas Walsh made it
known that once he took office,

00:16:53.970 --> 00:16:56.620
he was going to clean house and
that would be the end J. Edgar

00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:58.240
Hoover's reign.

00:16:58.240 --> 00:17:06.360
Unfortunately, before he could take
office, he was a 76 year old widow.

00:17:06.360 --> 00:17:12.020
He gets married in Miami to a Cuban
debutant, boards the train to come

00:17:12.020 --> 00:17:16.830
to Washington, but only makes
it as far as to North Carolina.

00:17:16.830 --> 00:17:22.990
And so with his death on the
train, Hoover escaped his sacking

00:17:22.990 --> 00:17:25.180
and the next attorney
general appointment,

00:17:25.180 --> 00:17:30.510
a fellow named Homer Cummings sees
some potential in Hoover and says,

00:17:30.510 --> 00:17:34.890
well we're going to hang on to you
but here's what you need to do.

00:17:34.890 --> 00:17:38.100
You need to show us something,
you need to, we need some kind

00:17:38.100 --> 00:17:42.560
of marquee case that can prove
that we should be the agency

00:17:42.560 --> 00:17:46.170
that should police the nation.

00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:50.570
And so Hoover immediately sets
out to do any number of things

00:17:50.570 --> 00:17:56.720
to launch his career, including
the capture of the prisoner

00:17:56.720 --> 00:18:00.560
who was killed Kansas
City's parking lot.

00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:04.220
So at this point, he's desperately
looking around for something

00:18:04.220 --> 00:18:05.950
that he could make his mark with.

00:18:05.950 --> 00:18:10.030
He's failed for 18 months to
solve the Lindbergh kidnapping

00:18:10.030 --> 00:18:13.330
which is lingering on and he's
been under a lot of pressure

00:18:13.330 --> 00:18:16.180
and been ridiculed for that.

00:18:16.180 --> 00:18:22.790
Nevertheless, he, he's always been
a guy who was interested in sort

00:18:22.790 --> 00:18:29.160
of furthering the scientific
approach to law enforcement.

00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:33.130
So what he does to combat
the scourge of kidnappings

00:18:33.130 --> 00:18:36.080
that are taking place,
is setup a hotline.

00:18:36.080 --> 00:18:41.660
It's about to be the first crime
hotline that was in the nation.

00:18:41.660 --> 00:18:45.220
So on this hotline you can
call and immediately be put

00:18:45.220 --> 00:18:48.860
through to the justice
department to report a kidnapping.

00:18:48.860 --> 00:18:52.700 position:56%
Hoover thinking that this gives his
agents an edge, because they can get

00:18:52.700 --> 00:18:54.820 position:56%
to the scene quickly and get control

00:18:54.820 --> 00:19:00.230
of the investigation before
the local cops take it over.

00:19:00.230 --> 00:19:05.850 position:56%
